g\"}','A','Oracle is primarily used for database management and enterprise applications.','2025-08-21 08:37:20','2025-08-21 08:37:20'),('question-012','lesson-028','What is the correct way to define a function in Python?','{\"A\": \"function myFunc():\", \"B\": \"def myFunc():\", \"C\": \"func myFunc():\", \"D\": \"define myFunc():\"}','B','In Python, functions are defined using the \'def\' keyword followed by the function name and parentheses.','2025-08-21 08:37:14','2025-08-21 08:37:14'),('question-013','lesson-028','Which of the following is a mutable data type in Python?','{\"A\": \"Tuple\", \"B\": \"String\", \"C\": \"List\", \"D\": \"Integer\"}','C','Lists are mutable in Python, meaning their contents can be changed after creation.','2025-08-21 08:37:14','2025-08-21 08:37:14'),('question-014','lesson-032','What is the primary purpose of database normalization?','{\"A\": \"Increase data redundancy\", \"B\": \"Reduce data redundancy\", \"C\": \"Slow down queries\", \"D\": \"Increase storage space\"}','B','Database normalization primarily aims to reduce data redundancy and improve data integrity.','2025-08-21 08:37:14','2025-08-21 08:37:14'),('question-015','lesson-032','What is a primary key?','{\"A\": \"A key that opens the database\", \"B\": \"A unique identifier for each record\", \"C\": \"The most important column\", \"D\": \"A password for the database\"}','B','A primary key is a unique identifier that ensures each record in a table can be uniquely identified.','2025-08-21 08:37:14','2025-08-21 08:37:14'),('question-016','lesson-034','What programming language is primarily used for Unity scripting?','{\"A\": \"JavaScript\", \"B\": \"Python\", \"C\": \"C#\", \"D\": \"Java\"}','C','C# is the primary programming language used for scripting in Unity game development.','2025-08-21 08:37:14','2025-08-21 08:37:14'),('question-017','lesson-034','What is a GameObject in Unity?','{\"A\": \"A game rule\", \"B\": \"A container for components\", \"C\": \"A player score\", \"D\": \"A game level\"}','B','A GameObject in Unity is a container that holds components, which define the object\'s behavior and properties.','2025-08-21 08:37:14','2025-08-21 08:37:14'),('question-018','lesson-038','What is a closure in JavaScript?','{\"A\": \"A way to close the browser\", \"B\": \"A function with access to outer scope variables\", \"C\": \"A type of loop\", \"D\": \"A JavaScript library\"}','B','A closure is a function that has access to variables in its outer (enclosing) scope even after the outer function has returned.','2025-08-21 08:37:14','2025-08-21 08:37:14'),('question-019','lesson-038','What does \'async/await\' help with in JavaScript?','{\"A\": \"Synchronous programming\", \"B\": \"Handling asynchronous operations\", \"C\": \"Variable declaration\", \"D\": \"DOM manipulation\"}','B','Async/await provides a cleaner way to handle asynchronous operations in JavaScript, making code more readable than promises.','2025-08-21 08:37:14','2025-08-21 08:37:14'),('question-02-003','lesson-012-01','What is a Python decorator?','{\"A\": \"A type of function\", \"B\": \"A design pattern\", \"C\": \"A way to modify functions\", \"D\": \"All of the above\"}','D','A Python decorator is a way to modify or enhance functions or methods without changing their code.','2025-08-21 08:37:19','2025-08-21 08:37:19'),('question-020','lesson-002','What is the virtual DOM in React?','{\"A\": \"A real DOM element\", \"B\": \"A JavaScript representation of the DOM\", \"C\": \"A browser feature\", \"D\": \"A database\"}','B','The virtual DOM is a JavaScript representation of the real DOM that React uses to optimize rendering performance.','2025-08-21 08:37:14','2025-08-21 08:37:14');
